===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|δραχμή||a drachma}}, from {{m|grc|δράσσομαι||to grasp, seize}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|drachmae|drachmai}}

# The currency of [[Greece]] from ancient times until 2001, with the symbol [[₯]], since replaced by the [[euro]].
# A coin worth one drachma.
# An [[Ancient Greek]] [[weight]] of about 66.5 [[grain]]s.
# A later [[Greek]] [[weight]] equal to a [[gram]].

